In Github: create new repository
In VScode: new window (so a fresh restart)
Git Clone repository (in command pallate), select the repo opened before
Where to store on drive
Save workspace (so all data will be together, even if few projects)
Now adding projects PlatformIO projects (can have one or more, for eample if seveal ESP32 projects are part of a larger project)
a. Add a PIO project
b. dont chose default folder, to have control on location
c. make changes 
d. stage all changes
e. Add comment and commit it
f. Synch or upload it all
